<!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.01 Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/html4/loose.dtd"><html>



<head>



<title>CREATE-WEALTH-HISTOGRAM</title>

</head>



<body>

	<h3><i>I set up and maintain a histogram of the distribution of sugar in the 

	population.</i> </h3>

	<font size="2" color="gray">Begin micro-behaviour</font>
	<p><b>CREATE-WEALTH-HISTOGRAM</b></p>

	<font size="2" color="gray">Begin NetLogo code:</font>
	<pre>create-histogram
  &quot;270&quot; &quot;450&quot;&nbsp;<i>; lower left corner</i>
  &quot;520&quot; &quot;709&quot;&nbsp;<i>; upper right corner</i>
  &quot;Wealth Histogram&quot;&nbsp;<i>; unique name (and label) for this plot</i>
  &quot;Wealth (tens of sugar)&quot;&nbsp;<i>; X axis label</i>
  &quot;Number of individuals&quot;&nbsp;<i>; Y axis label</i>
  all-individuals
  (round (my-sugar / 10))&nbsp;<i>; value being displayed</i>
  &quot;0&quot;&nbsp;<i>; minimum x value</i>
  &quot;20&quot;&nbsp;<i>; maximum x value</i>
  &quot;0&quot; &nbsp;<i>; minimum y value</i>
  &quot;100&quot;&nbsp;<i>; maximum y value</i>
</pre>

	<font size="2" color="gray">End NetLogo code</font>
	<h2>Variants</h2>

	<p>All the labels and parameters can be changed.</p>

	<p><i>Note that currently the system is limited to interpreting calls to 

	create-histogram where each argument is on a different line.</i></p>

	<h2>How this works</h2>

	<p>It computes the number of tens of sugar units each individual has by 

	dividing the sugar by ten and rounding.</p>

	<h2>Related Micro-behaviours</h2>


	<p>

	<a title="CREATE-POPULATION-PLOT" href="CREATE-POPULATION-PLOT.html">

	CREATE-POPULATION-PLOT</a> creates a plot of the population.</p>

